{{Quote|What is this?"<br />"Your honor guard, noble Obi-Wan. Don't you remember being promised a 'present' by the twinned Council of Alwari Elders? This is it. They didn't want anything to happen to their new offworld friends. Especially not before the formal treaty between the Alwari and the Unity is put in place. We've been shadowing you ever since you left our camp; guarding your rear, looking for trouble, watching out for you.|Bayaar, to Jedi Master Obi-Wan Kenobi and his companions|<ref name="The Approaching Storm">''[[The Approaching Storm]]''</ref>}}
The '''Situng Borokii''' were a branch of the [[Alwari]] [[Borokii]] [[overclan]] on [[Ansion/Legends|Ansion]]. Their warriors were considered to be the finest of all the Borokii and its subclans. It had a [[Gender/Legends|female]] representative on the [[Borokii Council of Elders]]. [[Bayaar]] was a sentry of the preeminent subclan, and he rose to eventually lead its prestigious guard.

In [[22 BBY/Legends|22 BBY]], at the conclusion of the [[Jedi/Legends|Jedi]] [[Border dispute on Ansion/Legends|mission to Ansion]], Bayaar was appointed captain of the elite Alwari [[honor guard]] that was gifted to the [[Jedi Order/Legends|Jedi]] [[Diplomat/Legends|diplomats]] from [[Coruscant/Legends|Coruscant]] who had come to achieve an accord between the [[Ansionian]] urbanites and the Alwari tribes, one that would protect the planet from [[Separatist Crisis/Legends|secession]] and ensure its retention within the [[Galactic Republic/Legends|Galactic Republic]].

'''The Alwari honor guard''', charged to shadow and protect the Jedi at all costs until they had seen the Ansionian secession vote of the representatives of the [[Unity of Community]] to its conclusion, was composed not only of the Situng Borokii's finest [[Soldier/Legends|soldiers]], but also of those of the [[Hovsgol Januul]], the preeminent subclan of Borokii-overclan rival, the [[Januul]]. In the [[Cuipernam]] [[Second skirmish in Cuipernam|skirmish]] with [[Soergg Vosadii Bezhin|Soergg]] the [[Hutt/Legends|Hutt's]] [[Mercenary/Legends|mercenary]] [[Bounty hunter/Legends|hunters]] and [[Sniper/Legends|snipers]], the Situng Borokii warriors fought side by side their once feuding tribal enemies, now their elite brethren, of the Hovsgol Januul. Because of the honor guard's valiant defense, the Jedi were able to overcome their malicious assailants and meet at last with the [[Unity Council]], who accepted the Alwari accord. Ansion voted to remain with the Republic, and the Jedi found successful closure to a critical mission.

